'''Homeless ministry''' is the intentional interaction between [[Christians]] and [[homeless]] persons, regardless of their faith. The ministering typically occurs in the environment in which the homeless reside. It may include distribution of provisions such as [[food]], [[clothing]], and blankets. The [[Mission (Christian)|ministry]] often involves building relationships with the homeless and providing them with information and [[relational care]]. [[Prayer]], conversation, and ministering to [[spirtuality|spiritual]] needs are part of the process.<ref>Scott, Daniel David, ''Homeless Ministry: In the Trenches'', [[Candler School of Theology]], National Institute in Church Finance and Administration, [[Emory University]], Atlanta Georgia, 1990.</ref> ==See also== *[[Homelessness]] *[[Volxkuche]] ==References== {{reflist}}
